FBIS4-62268 "drsov093_n_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-093 Daily Report 13 May 1994 Turkmenistan Parliament Discusses Niyazov Plan to Encourage Savings Parliament Discusses Niyazov Plan to Encourage Savings LD1305100194 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel Network in Russian 0800 GMT 13 May 94 LD1305100194 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel Network Russian BFN [From the "Novosti" newscast] [Text] A three-year program for Turkmenistan's socioeconomic development was proposed at today's meeting of the republican parliament in Ashgabat. Our correspondent says it was drafted by President Niyazov. The program is entitled "10 Years of Prosperity" and contains specific presidential proposals. These include, for example, the idea that there should be a change in the ratio between the proportion of wages devoted to living expenses and the proportion set aside as savings. The leaders of contemporary Turkmenistan claim that citizens should be able to save 30-40 percent of their income and that all the necessary conditions have been created in the Republic for this.
